$JAMF JAMF has been growing rapidly and leading in this space for many years now alongside both the $AAPL and $MSFT products. For those who have done some amount of DD, the idea that both Apple and Microsoft have ineffective products in this space is very telling. This is a highly specialized, and high touch, space where only a smaller company like Jamf that focuses 100% on this niche can serve the rapidly evolving needs of the market. Huge companies like Apple/Microsoft can plant a flag in the ground in this space, but they can't do what Jamf does. There is no ROI for the amount of resources that Apple/Microsoft would have to commit to competing with Jamf. Truth is that Jamf is likely an M&A target for one of these two larger companies, if they want to become the Best In Class competitor in this space, then they would have to acquire or partner with Jamf. Until then, Jamf will continue to grow rapidly in this space that they currently dominate. The $55 Needham target will be raised.
